What you need to know:

Abdallah al-Thani "submitted his resignation late Sunday at a meeting with parliament speaker Aguila Saleh", spokesman Ezzedine el-Faleh said in a statement received by AFP.Libya, which sits on the continent's biggest crude oil reserves, has endured almost a decade of violent chaos since the NATO-backed uprising against Kadhafi.The United Nations Support Mission in Libya on Monday expressed "grave concern regarding reports that one civilian was killed, three were injured, and a number of other demonstrators arrested" in Al-Marj.